</taxonomicName>
by monotypy.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97A286C19695846202A380DA144F0DB" blockId="37.[113,1090,616,1631]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846202A380DA2FAF05B" bold="true" box="[113,412,616,639]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Distinguishing characters.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584621F8380DA29FF05B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[419,505,616,639]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584621F8380DA29FF05B" box="[419,505,616,639]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having a subquadratic (
<figureCitation id="71FE34E9196958462396380DA77CF05B" box="[973,1050,616,639]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="8.[151,188,1381,1400]" captionTargetBox="[175,1099,219,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[174,1104,219,1322]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1–11. Dorsal habitus. 1 – Homalispa batesii Baly, 1858, French Guyana: Mt. Kaw; 2 – Cyclantispa gracilis (Baly, 1885), Panama: La Fortuna; 3 –Xanthispa cimicoides (Guérin-Méneville, 1844), French Guyana: Le Larivot; 4 – Imatidium thoracicum Fabricius, 1801, Ecuador: Cascada San Rafael; 5 – Aslamidium (s. str.) capense (Herbst, 1799), French Guyana: Fourgassie; 6 – Aslamidium (Neoaslamidium) pichinchaensis Borowiec, 1998, Ecuador: Puerto Misahuallí; 7 – Calliaspis sachaensis Borowiec &amp; Stojczew, 1998, Ecuador: Shushu¿ndi; 8 – Spaethaspis lloydi Hincks, 1952, Ecuador: Río Puno. 9 – Xenispa testaceicornis (Pic, 1926), Bolivia: Refugio Los Volcanes; 10 – Xenispa costaricensis (Uhmann, 1930), Panama:La Fortuna;11 – Euxema insignis Baly, 1858, syntype, Panama: Volcan de Barú. All scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301734/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) or semicircular (
<figureCitation id="71FE34E919695846215A38EDA259F0BB" box="[257,319,648,671]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="8.[151,188,1381,1400]" captionTargetBox="[175,1099,219,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[174,1104,219,1322]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1–11. Dorsal habitus. 1 – Homalispa batesii Baly, 1858, French Guyana: Mt. Kaw; 2 – Cyclantispa gracilis (Baly, 1885), Panama: La Fortuna; 3 –Xanthispa cimicoides (Guérin-Méneville, 1844), French Guyana: Le Larivot; 4 – Imatidium thoracicum Fabricius, 1801, Ecuador: Cascada San Rafael; 5 – Aslamidium (s. str.) capense (Herbst, 1799), French Guyana: Fourgassie; 6 – Aslamidium (Neoaslamidium) pichinchaensis Borowiec, 1998, Ecuador: Puerto Misahuallí; 7 – Calliaspis sachaensis Borowiec &amp; Stojczew, 1998, Ecuador: Shushu¿ndi; 8 – Spaethaspis lloydi Hincks, 1952, Ecuador: Río Puno. 9 – Xenispa testaceicornis (Pic, 1926), Bolivia: Refugio Los Volcanes; 10 – Xenispa costaricensis (Uhmann, 1930), Panama:La Fortuna;11 – Euxema insignis Baly, 1858, syntype, Panama: Volcan de Barú. All scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301734/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) pronotum with an emarginate apical margin above the head, prognathous but not projecting mouthparts, and the serrate lateroapical margins of elytra. 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584623E038CDA777F09B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1885" box="[955,1041,680,703]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Euxema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584623E038CDA777F09B" box="[955,1041,680,703]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Euxema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846202A38ADA3B6F0FB" authority="Sekerka, 2014" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2014" box="[113,208,712,735]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Katkispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846202A38ADA3B6F0FB" box="[113,208,712,735]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Katkispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C082490519695846208238ADA25AF0FB" box="[217,316,712,735]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are the only similar genera, but both differ in the apical margin of the pronotum being convex, not emarginate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1DF7BE719695846202A396DA17EF7BB" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E97A286C19695846202A396DA167F6BB" blockId="37.[113,1090,616,1631]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846202A396DA386F13B" bold="true" box="[113,224,776,799]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1969584620BD396DA20FF13B" author="BALY J. S." box="[230,361,776,799]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" refId="ref28592" refString="BALY J. S. 1858: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Order of the Trustees, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1858">BALY (1858)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the genus for a single species, 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF196958462342396DA0FFF13B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[793,921,776,799]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E196958462342396DA0FFF13B" box="[793,921,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">X. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1969584623FE396DA727F13B" author="WEISE J." box="[933,1089,776,799]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" pagination="67 - 127" refId="ref32532" refString="WEISE J. 1910 b: Beitrag zur Kenntnis der amerikanischen Hispinen. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 76: 67 - 127." type="journal article" year="1910">WEISE (1910b)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF196958462152394DA239F11B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[265,351,808,831]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E196958462152394DA239F11B" box="[265,351,808,831]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584621F9394DA170F11B" authorityName="sensu MOROS &amp; VIANA" authorityYear="1947" box="[418,534,808,831]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Demotispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584621F9394DA170F11B" box="[418,534,808,831]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Demotispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and proposed a replacement name, 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584623FE394DA774F11B" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1910" box="[933,1042,808,831]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Demotispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584623FE394DA774F11B" box="[933,1042,808,831]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">D. magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846202A392DA2D6F17B" authority="Baly, 1858" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[113,432,840,863]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846202A392DA254F17B" box="[113,306,840,863]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa pulchella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D196958462162392DA2D6F17B" author="BALY J. S." box="[313,432,840,863]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" refId="ref28592" refString="BALY J. S. 1858: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Order of the Trustees, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1858">Baly, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584621BF392DA05BF17B" authority="Baly, 1858" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[484,829,840,863]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Demotispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584621BF392DA1A4F17B" box="[484,706,840,863]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Demotispa pulchella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D196958462291392DA05BF17B" author="BALY J. S." box="[714,829,840,863]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" refId="ref28592" refString="BALY J. S. 1858: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Order of the Trustees, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1858">Baly, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but never examined the 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE19695846202A390DA3C4F15B" box="[113,162,872,895]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">type</typeStatus>
. This was followed until 
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1969584621F5390DA12DF15B" author="STAINES C. L." box="[430,587,872,895]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref31701" refString="STAINES C. L. 2009: Generic reassignment of species in the tribe Cephaloleiini Chapuis, 1875 (Coleoptera: Cassidinae). Insecta Mundi 107: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="2009">STAINES (2009)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF196958462297390DA053F15B" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1910" box="[716,821,872,895]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Demotispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E196958462297390DA053F15B" box="[716,821,872,895]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">D. magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846230C390DA3CFF1BB" authority="Spaeth, 1938" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Parimatidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846230C390DA08DF15B" box="[855,1003,872,895]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Parimatidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D1969584623AA390DA3CFF1BB" author="SPAETH F." pageId="37" pageNumber="294" pagination="305 - 317" refId="ref31335" refString="SPAETH F. 1938: Die Gattung Himatidium Fabr. (Col. Cassidinae). Revista de Entomologia 9: 305 - 317." type="journal article" year="1938">Spaeth, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, however did not proposed synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846222A39EDA1A1F1BB" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[625,711,904,927]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846222A39EDA1A1F1BB" box="[625,711,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846235C39EDA0FDF1BB" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1938" box="[775,923,904,927]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Parimatidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846235C39EDA0FDF1BB" box="[775,923,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Parimatidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor mentioned existence of that genus, although 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846218439CDA153F19B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[479,565,936,959]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846218439CDA153F19B" box="[479,565,936,959]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had a priority because of being the older name. 
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D19695846202A39ADA276F1FB" author="STAINES C. L." box="[113,272,968,991]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref31701" refString="STAINES C. L. 2009: Generic reassignment of species in the tribe Cephaloleiini Chapuis, 1875 (Coleoptera: Cassidinae). Insecta Mundi 107: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="2009">STAINES (2009)</bibRefCitation>
also transferred all 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584621B639ADA1D0F1FB" box="[493,694,968,991]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Demotispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584621B639ADA107F1FB" box="[493,609,968,991]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Demotispa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with serrate lateroapical margins of elytra to 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846208E398DA20FF1DB" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1938" box="[213,361,1000,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Parimatidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846208E398DA20FF1DB" box="[213,361,1000,1023]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Parimatidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, not a single one of these species is actually congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584620FC3E6DA2F4F63B" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1850" box="[167,402,1032,1055]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Parimatidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrum">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584620FC3E6DA2F4F63B" box="[167,402,1032,1055]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Parimatidium rubrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE19695846219D3E6DA292F63B" box="[454,500,1032,1055]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">type</typeStatus>
species, as it has tarsal claws with basal tooth while all transferred species have simple tarsal claws. Hence, I restore the status of 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584623FA3E4DA091F61B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[929,1015,1064,1087]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584623FA3E4DA091F61B" box="[929,1015,1064,1087]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has serrate lateroapical margins of the elytra, simple tarsal claws, and metallic elytra. Some species transferred here to 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF1969584621CE3E0DA28DF65B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[405,491,1128,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584621CE3E0DA28DF65B" box="[405,491,1128,1151]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have to be considered as tentative placements, as I did not examine their 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE1969584621683EEDA20DF6BB" box="[307,363,1160,1183]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">types</typeStatus>
(see 
<tableCitation id="A4471DD71969584621F83EEDA297F6BB" box="[419,497,1160,1183]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="20.[113,160,425,444]" captionText="Table 1. Summary of placements of species included in genera Demotispa Baly, 1858, Parimatidium Spaeth, 1938, Stilpnaspis Weise, 1905. TP states for tentative" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97A286C1969584620CB3ECDA0EBF77B" blockId="37.[113,1090,616,1631]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E1969584620CB3ECDA385F69B" box="[144,227,1192,1215]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xensipa</emphasis>
species can be divided into two groups on the basis of pronotal shape, thus is placed doubly in the key. About eight species have semicircular pronota (
<figureCitation id="71FE34E919695846235D3EADA024F6FB" box="[774,834,1224,1247]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="8.[151,188,1381,1400]" captionTargetBox="[175,1099,219,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[174,1104,219,1322]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1–11. Dorsal habitus. 1 – Homalispa batesii Baly, 1858, French Guyana: Mt. Kaw; 2 – Cyclantispa gracilis (Baly, 1885), Panama: La Fortuna; 3 –Xanthispa cimicoides (Guérin-Méneville, 1844), French Guyana: Le Larivot; 4 – Imatidium thoracicum Fabricius, 1801, Ecuador: Cascada San Rafael; 5 – Aslamidium (s. str.) capense (Herbst, 1799), French Guyana: Fourgassie; 6 – Aslamidium (Neoaslamidium) pichinchaensis Borowiec, 1998, Ecuador: Puerto Misahuallí; 7 – Calliaspis sachaensis Borowiec &amp; Stojczew, 1998, Ecuador: Shushu¿ndi; 8 – Spaethaspis lloydi Hincks, 1952, Ecuador: Río Puno. 9 – Xenispa testaceicornis (Pic, 1926), Bolivia: Refugio Los Volcanes; 10 – Xenispa costaricensis (Uhmann, 1930), Panama:La Fortuna;11 – Euxema insignis Baly, 1858, syntype, Panama: Volcan de Barú. All scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301734/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) while the rest, including the 
<typeStatus id="367E96CE1969584620CE3E8DA3A7F6DB" box="[149,193,1256,1279]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">type</typeStatus>
species, have subquadratic and parallel-sided pronota (
<figureCitation id="71FE34E91969584622B93E8DA04DF6DB" box="[738,811,1256,1279]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="8.[151,188,1381,1400]" captionTargetBox="[175,1099,219,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-10@8.[174,1104,219,1322]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 1–11. Dorsal habitus. 1 – Homalispa batesii Baly, 1858, French Guyana: Mt. Kaw; 2 – Cyclantispa gracilis (Baly, 1885), Panama: La Fortuna; 3 –Xanthispa cimicoides (Guérin-Méneville, 1844), French Guyana: Le Larivot; 4 – Imatidium thoracicum Fabricius, 1801, Ecuador: Cascada San Rafael; 5 – Aslamidium (s. str.) capense (Herbst, 1799), French Guyana: Fourgassie; 6 – Aslamidium (Neoaslamidium) pichinchaensis Borowiec, 1998, Ecuador: Puerto Misahuallí; 7 – Calliaspis sachaensis Borowiec &amp; Stojczew, 1998, Ecuador: Shushu¿ndi; 8 – Spaethaspis lloydi Hincks, 1952, Ecuador: Río Puno. 9 – Xenispa testaceicornis (Pic, 1926), Bolivia: Refugio Los Volcanes; 10 – Xenispa costaricensis (Uhmann, 1930), Panama:La Fortuna;11 – Euxema insignis Baly, 1858, syntype, Panama: Volcan de Barú. All scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301734/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Species with subquadratic pronota can be further split in to two groups, one with broadly explanate margins of the pronotum and the other with narrow margins of the pronotum. However, other morphological features as well as their biology are similar, thus I retain all the species in the same genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97A286C19695846202A3F0DA13FF75B" blockId="37.[113,1090,616,1631]" box="[113,601,1383,1407]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846202A3F0DA2B6F75B" bold="true" box="[113,464,1383,1407]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
Species transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846212B3F02A2AFF75B" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1858" box="[368,457,1383,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846212B3F02A2AFF75B" bold="true" box="[368,457,1383,1407]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
See 
<tableCitation id="A4471DD71969584622583F0DA135F75B" box="[515,595,1384,1407]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="20.[113,160,425,444]" captionText="Table 1. Summary of placements of species included in genera Demotispa Baly, 1858, Parimatidium Spaeth, 1938, Stilpnaspis Weise, 1905. TP states for tentative" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97A286C19695846202A3FEDA17EF7BB" blockId="37.[113,1090,616,1631]" box="[113,536,1416,1439]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846202A3FEDA22FF7BB" bold="true" box="[113,329,1416,1439]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Number of species.</emphasis>
33 (present paper).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1DF7BE719695846202A3FCDA095F43B" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="E97A286C19695846202A3FCDA095F43B" blockId="37.[113,1090,616,1631]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846202A3FCDA3AAF79B" bold="true" box="[113,204,1448,1471]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Biology.</emphasis>
So far, only three species have published host plant associations, two with bambusoid 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846202A3FADA3AEF7FB" baseAuthorityName="BONDAR" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[113,200,1480,1503]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D19695846208E3FADA20AF7FB" author="UHMANN E." box="[213,364,1480,1503]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" pagination="611 - 630" refId="ref32254" refString="UHMANN E. 1959: Amerikanische Hispinae aus den Sammlungen amerikanischer Entomologen. 199. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Hispinae (Coleopt. Chrysomelidae). Pesquisas, Seria Zoologia 3: 611 - 630." type="journal article" year="1959">UHMANN 1959</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D19695846212E3FADA126F7FB" author="MESKINS C. &amp; WINDSOR D. &amp; HANCE T." box="[373,576,1480,1503]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref30750" refString="MESKINS C., WINDSOR D. &amp; HANCE T. 2008: A comparison of hispine beetles (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae) associated with three orders of monocot host plants in lowland Panama. International Journal of Tropical Insect Science 27: 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="2008">MESKINS et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and one with 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846228F3FADA09EF7FB" authority="(BONDAR 1940 b)" baseAuthorityName="BONDAR" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[724,1016,1480,1503]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Arecaceae (
<bibRefCitation id="8D54559D19695846230B3FADA096F7FB" author="BONDAR G." box="[848,1008,1480,1503]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref28897" refString="BONDAR G. 1940 b: Insectos nocivos e molestias do coqueiro (Cocos nucifera) no Brasil. Boletim do Instituto Central de Fomento Economico de Bahia 8: 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1940">BONDAR 1940b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Based on our ¿eld observations it seems that most species are associated with various bambusoid 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846202A3C6DA3ADF43B" baseAuthorityName="BONDAR" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[113,203,1544,1567]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
, mainly 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846217C3C6DA2F4F43B" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1822" box="[295,402,1544,1567]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Chusquea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846217C3C6DA2F4F43B" box="[295,402,1544,1567]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Chusquea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2EC553EF19695846219E3C6DA109F43B" box="[453,623,1544,1567]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Guadua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="DBB1F47E19695846219E3C6DA17DF43B" box="[453,539,1544,1567]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">Guadua</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(Windsor &amp; Sekerka, unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1DF7BE719695846202A3C4DA0D0F41B" box="[113,950,1576,1599]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294" type="key">
<paragraph id="E97A286C19695846202A3C4DA0D0F41B" blockId="37.[113,1090,616,1631]" box="[113,950,1576,1599]" pageId="37" pageNumber="294">
